                  </persName>
            . On the evening of the 17th of December, about six o'clock, I was in Gee's-court, and saw the prisoners - I heard Cairn say to Grindley,</p>
               <p>"This is the shop;" he was just by a dealer in marine stores - they walked in; I followed, and heard the man in the shop, say,</p>
               <p>"I don't buy." I asked what they had got, and found a piece of lead concealed under Grindley's coat, and a piece on Cairn - it corresponded exactly with the roof. I secured them.</p>
